# Testing Instructions

- Write tests around observable behavior, not private implementation details.
- Cover happy path, edge cases, and failure cases for changed code.
- Mock external systems in unit tests; do not call real services.
- Keep fixtures and setup minimal so failures stay easy to diagnose.
- Use the project test commands documented in `CLAUDE.md`.
